Create some nice links in one or more .page files here, you can create a
link by using
__[_fake_[<<URL>>][<<name>>]]

Note that a link must be on a complete line without line breaks.

If you want to specify an external link, you can just use http:// in the url.

You can also link to pages in the same site by using ":<<id>>" instead of an URL:
__[_fake_[:documentation][]]

If you do not specify a name, the page name will be used. See the page.attr
entry in [[:file_types][]] for an explanation about page ids.

There's an optional third argument to page link entries, if you specify
__[_fake_[<<URL>>][<<name>>][<<extra>>]],
the <<extra>> part will be copied directly into the <<a>> tag of the HTML page.
This way, you can for instance put in a css class.
